Syroq 52 wizard</font><P>SyrSpyder<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucorvan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Corvan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://gucomics.everlore.com/coolstuff/sigpic_07mini.jpg BORDER=0></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Apprentice</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5/16/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>3:06:01 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.members.home.net/testuart/sigpic_18mini.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Duels - Spells memed</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Speaking as a chanter, I can tell you that they're a rough class to face as a wizard.  While their offence is weak, they can render you harmless with ease.  <br>
<br>
At lower levels they'll just mana sieve you, and it's a matter of resists and your mana pool that determines whether you manage to kill them before you run OOM.  Once you're OOM, they can keep you that way and just wear you down with a pet.<br>
<br>
At the highest levels (59+), they'll just rapture you and then sieve you dry.  Rapture is unresistable in duels.  An enchanter only has magic based nukes and it's very easy to get your MR up to the point where they can't touch you.  However, it is highly difficult to keep that chanter pet or (worse yet) a charmed mob off of you when you're OOM, unable to sit down to med, and being sieved occasionally so that you can't even count on standing regen to get you enough for a root.  (A good enchanter will have cast resist magic on their pet so you'd have to debuff it before having a good chance of rooting it anyways)  <br>
<br>
I haven't seen a strategy that works against an enchanter who knows to use Mana Sieve.  The ones that want to debuff (i.e. Cripple, weaken, etc) you, fear you, and otherwise do other resistable things will be cake unless your MR is too low.  <br>
<br>
If it's any consolation, while a competent enchanter will beat a wizard almost all the time, they have extreme problems with meelee classes such as warriors.  Without a suitably strong NPC at hand to charm, they're in a world of pain.<br>
